95.0: All of the coatings were highly transparent and even the sample that contained 9.7 wt% of PDMS and was 42 µm thick had a transmittance value of 95%.

93.0: The article does not contain any transmittance graphs for the PTES-treated SiO2-coated ZnO nanorods sample but it is written that the transmittance was approximately 45% (average) in the UV region and on the order of 93–95% across the visible region.

95.0: Even PF-TMMS exhibited high transmittance (> 95%), but the transmittance of PF-TMMS was decreased by introducing the fluorine moiety because the fluorinated silica particles could scatter light.
